techmeme.title: Qualcomm reports Q1 revenue up 17% YoY to $11.67B, vs. $10.93B est., handsets revenue up 13% to $7.57B, net income up 15% to $3.18B, issues a strong Q2 guidance (Kif Leswing/CNBC)
Sources: SoftBank is in advanced talks to acquire Ampere in a deal that could value the Oracle-backed chip designer at about $6.5B, including debt (Bloomberg)
Amazon announces an event on February 26 in New York where, according to sources, the company will preview its long-delayed Alexa generative AI revamp (Greg Bensinger/Reuters)
Sources: banks sold $5.5B in debt borrowed by X at $0.97 on the dollar, following strong investor demand; they had planned to sell ~$3B at ~$0.95 on the dollar (Wall Street Journal)
MicroStrategy announces a new name, Strategy, a new logo with a stylized "B", signifying its bitcoin strategy, and orange as the brand's primary color (Jason Shubnell/The Block)
